  "profile": {
    "id": "u01_priyansh",
    "user_name": "Priyansh",
    "profession": "Software engineer at a fintech",
    "mother_tongue": "Hindi",
    "interests": "Cricket, Bollywood movies, Startups",
    "engagement": "medium",
    "english_level": "B1",
    "personality": "curious but reserved; thinks before replying; warms up after a few turns"
  },
  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Priyansh, I'm Miss Maya. Honestly, I love how warm weather makes evenings so cozy, what's your favorite thing to do in the evening?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hmm, I usually watch a movie or listen to music. Sometimes I go for a short cricket game with friends. What about you?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That sounds fun. I usually enjoy a good movie or some light music in the evening. What kind of movies do you like?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I like Bollywood movies the most. The music and stories are very nice. Sometimes I watch some Hollywood too, but Hindi movies are more my cup of tea. Do you watch movies often?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "I watch movies often, Bollywood is a favorite too. The stories and music are so vibrant. What’s your all time favorite Bollywood film?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "My all-time favorite is \"Dilwale Dulhania Le Jayenge\". It's a classic, you know? The story is very emotional and the music is amazing. Have you seen it?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Got it, DDLJ is a true classic. The song \"Mere Meri Pehli Baarish\" always stands out. Do you prefer old Bollywood or the newer ones?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I like both, but old Bollywood has more soul, you know? The songs are more memorable. Though some new movies are good too, like \"Gully Cricket\". Have you seen it?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "I get what you mean about old Bollywood, the songs really stick with you. Gully Cricket sounds fun, I’ll have to check it out. What’s your favorite old Bollywood song?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "It's hard to pick one, but \"Tum Hi Ho\" from \"Aashiqui 2\" is special. The emotion in the song is very powerful. My mom loves old songs like \"Lag Ja Gale\" too. Maybe I should listen to them more often."
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Tum Hi Ho\" is a beautiful choice, it’s hard to beat that kind of emotion. \"Lag Ja Gale\" is timeless too. What made you decide to listen to more old songs?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Actually, I just started rediscovering old songs because my mom plays them a lot at home. It reminds me of childhood, you know? The melodies feel more... *dil se*, if I can say. I think I want to connect with that feeling more."
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That’s a lovely way to connect with the past. \"Dil se\", yes, those songs touch the heart. What’s one memory that comes to mind when you hear them?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "One memory is sitting with my family during Diwali, listening to old songs on the radio. The whole house would sing along, and it felt like everything was glowing—*literally* and *metaphorically*. Those moments feel so full of love."
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That sounds truly special, family, music, and Diwali lights all blending. What’s your favorite part of Diwali?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "My favorite part is lighting the fireworks with my cousins. It’s chaotic but fun. And, of course, the sweets! My favorite is *gulab jamun*. But the whole feeling of the festival, the lights, the *garmi* of being with family—it’s all so nice."
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "I get that, the chaos, the sweets, the warmth of family. What’s your go to Diwali snack besides gulab jamun?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I usually have *barfi* or *kheer* with tea. Sometimes we make *ladoo* at home. Honestly, any sweet is good for me, but *gulab jamun* is the ultimate Diwali treat. You?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "I love kheer too, it’s the perfect comfort. Gulab jamun definitely steals the show though. What’s your favorite way to eat it, hot or cold?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 11,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Honestly, I prefer it hot, the syrup is all melty and soft. But sometimes we soak it in syrup for hours and eat it cold too. Both are good, but hot feels better during Diwali, *you know?*"
    },
    {
      "turn": 11,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hot gulab jamun hits just right with the cold tea. What’s your go to tea choice for Diwali?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 12,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I usually have masala chai with Diwali sweets. The spices like cardamom and cinnamon go really well with the sweetness. My mom always makes it extra strong. It’s the perfect mix—*dil se*."
    },
    {
      "turn": 12,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Masala chai is the soul of Diwali, that perfect blend of spices and warmth. What’s your favorite part of helping out with Diwali prep at home?"
    }
  ],
